  "response": "There are no surviving contemporary portraits of Chhatrapati Shivaji Maharaj drawn or authorized by Mir Muhammad. Most of the well-known depictions and paintings of Shivaji Maharaj have been created much later by various artists, based on descriptions and artistic interpretations. If you come across a painting claimed to be by Mir Muhammad, it's likely a reproduction or an artistic representation rather than an original contemporary work. Historical depictions of significant figures like Shivaji Maharaj often rely on artistic imagination and descriptions from texts and chroniclers of that era.",
